{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1121,"text":"So, embryonic stem cells"},{"time":4110,"text":"are really incredible cells."},{"time":7410,"text":"They are our body's own repair kits,"},{"time":10198,"text":"and they're pluripotent, which means they can morph into"},{"time":13162,"text":"all of the cells in our bodies."},{"time":15594,"text":"Soon, we actually will be able to use stem cells"},{"time":18282,"text":"to replace cells that are damaged or diseased."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21267,"text":"But that's not what I want to talk to you about,"},{"time":23698,"text":"because right now there are some really"},{"time":26376,"text":"extraordinary things that we are doing with stem cells"},{"time":30322,"text":"that are completely changing"},{"time":31929,"text":"the way we look and model disease,"},{"time":34828,"text":"our ability to understand why we get sick,"},{"time":37347,"text":"and even develop drugs."},{"time":39778,"text":"I truly believe that stem cell research is going to allow"},{"time":44091,"text":"our children to look at Alzheimer's and diabetes"},{"time":48596,"text":"and other major diseases the way we view polio today,"},{"time":52987,"text":"which is as a preventable disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56188,"text":"So here we have this incredible field, which has"},{"time":59411,"text":"enormous hope for humanity,"},{"time":63798,"text":"but much like IVF over 35 years ago,"},{"time":67318,"text":"until the birth of a healthy baby, Louise,"},{"time":69652,"text":"this field has been under siege politically and financially."},{"time":74721,"text":"Critical research is being challenged instead of supported,"},{"time":78993,"text":"and we saw that it was really essential to have"},{"time":83353,"text":"private safe haven laboratories where this work"},{"time":86884,"text":"could be advanced without interference."},{"time":89714,"text":"And so, in 2005,"},{"time":92245,"text":"we started the New York Stem Cell Foundation Laboratory"},{"time":94857,"text":"so that we would have a small organization that could"},{"time":98446,"text":"do this work and support it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101758,"text":"What we saw very quickly is the world of both medical"},{"time":105143,"text":"research, but also developing drugs and treatments,"},{"time":108519,"text":"is dominated by, as you would expect, large organizations,"},{"time":112232,"text":"but in a new field, sometimes large organizations"},{"time":115351,"text":"really have trouble getting out of their own way,"},{"time":117519,"text":"and sometimes they can't ask the right questions,"},{"time":119955,"text":"and there is an enormous gap that's just gotten larger"},{"time":123311,"text":"between academic research on the one hand"},{"time":126522,"text":"and pharmaceutical companies and biotechs"},{"time":129223,"text":"that are responsible for delivering all of our drugs"},{"time":132489,"text":"and many of our treatments, and so we knew that"},{"time":134879,"text":"to really accelerate cures and therapies, we were going"},{"time":138825,"text":"to have to address this with two things:"},{"time":141632,"text":"new technologies and also a new research model."},{"time":144854,"text":"Because if you don't close that gap, you really are"},{"time":148613,"text":"exactly where we are today."},{"time":150220,"text":"And that's what I want to focus on."},{"time":151887,"text":"We've spent the last couple of years pondering this,"},{"time":155437,"text":"making a list of the different things that we had to do,"},{"time":157828,"text":"and so we developed a new technology,"},{"time":160459,"text":"It's software and hardware,"},{"time":161710,"text":"that actually can generate thousands and thousands of"},{"time":165213,"text":"genetically diverse stem cell lines to create"},{"time":168383,"text":"a global array, essentially avatars of ourselves."},{"time":172170,"text":"And we did this because we think that it's actually going"},{"time":175604,"text":"to allow us to realize the potential, the promise,"},{"time":179019,"text":"of all of the sequencing of the human genome,"},{"time":182099,"text":"but it's going to allow us, in doing that,"},{"time":184603,"text":"to actually do clinical trials in a dish with human cells,"},{"time":189611,"text":"not animal cells, to generate drugs and treatments"},{"time":193770,"text":"that are much more effective, much safer,"},{"time":197019,"text":"much faster, and at a much lower cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200275,"text":"So let me put that in perspective for you"},{"time":202659,"text":"and give you some context."},{"time":204075,"text":"This is an extremely new field."},{"time":208907,"text":"In 1998, human embryonic stem cells"},{"time":211739,"text":"were first identified, and just nine years later,"},{"time":215251,"text":"a group of scientists in Japan were able to take skin cells"},{"time":219556,"text":"and reprogram them with very powerful viruses"},{"time":222751,"text":"to create a kind of pluripotent stem cell"},{"time":226993,"text":"called an induced pluripotent stem cell,"},{"time":229083,"text":"or what we refer to as an IPS cell."},{"time":232091,"text":"This was really an extraordinary advance, because"},{"time":235289,"text":"although these cells are not human embryonic stem cells,"},{"time":237833,"text":"which still remain the gold standard,"},{"time":239627,"text":"they are terrific to use for modeling disease"},{"time":243097,"text":"and potentially for drug discovery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245827,"text":"So a few months later, in 2008, one of our scientists"},{"time":248867,"text":"built on that research. He took skin biopsies,"},{"time":252067,"text":"this time from people who had a disease,"},{"time":254095,"text":"ALS, or as you call it in the U.K., motor neuron disease."},{"time":257009,"text":"He turned them into the IPS cells"},{"time":258707,"text":"that I've just told you about, and then he turned those"},{"time":261393,"text":"IPS cells into the motor neurons that actually"},{"time":264097,"text":"were dying in the disease."},{"time":265558,"text":"So basically what he did was to take a healthy cell"},{"time":268577,"text":"and turn it into a sick cell,"},{"time":270291,"text":"and he recapitulated the disease over and over again"},{"time":273849,"text":"in the dish, and this was extraordinary,"},{"time":277209,"text":"because it was the first time that we had a model"},{"time":279457,"text":"of a disease from a living patient in living human cells."},{"time":283645,"text":"And as he watched the disease unfold, he was able"},{"time":286765,"text":"to discover that actually the motor neurons were dying"},{"time":289776,"text":"in the disease in a different way than the field"},{"time":291903,"text":"had previously thought. There was another kind of cell"},{"time":294397,"text":"that actually was sending out a toxin"},{"time":296598,"text":"and contributing to the death of these motor neurons,"},{"time":299109,"text":"and you simply couldn't see it"},{"time":300467,"text":"until you had the human model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302257,"text":"So you could really say that"},{"time":304924,"text":"researchers trying to understand the cause of disease"},{"time":308830,"text":"without being able to have human stem cell models"},{"time":312982,"text":"were much like investigators trying to figure out"},{"time":315742,"text":"what had gone terribly wrong in a plane crash"},{"time":318983,"text":"without having a black box, or a flight recorder."},{"time":322980,"text":"They could hypothesize about what had gone wrong,"},{"time":325582,"text":"but they really had no way of knowing what led"},{"time":328694,"text":"to the terrible events."},{"time":330866,"text":"And stem cells really have given us the black box"},{"time":335049,"text":"for diseases, and it's an unprecedented window."},{"time":339017,"text":"It really is extraordinary, because you can recapitulate"},{"time":342262,"text":"many, many diseases in a dish, you can see"},{"time":345509,"text":"what begins to go wrong in the cellular conversation"},{"time":349045,"text":"well before you would ever see"},{"time":351469,"text":"symptoms appear in a patient."},{"time":354005,"text":"And this opens up the ability,"},{"time":356528,"text":"which hopefully will become something that"},{"time":359342,"text":"is routine in the near term,"},{"time":361989,"text":"of using human cells to test for drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366135,"text":"Right now, the way we test for drugs is pretty problematic."},{"time":371599,"text":"To bring a successful drug to market, it takes, on average,"},{"time":374917,"text":"13 years — that's one drug —"},{"time":377103,"text":"with a sunk cost of 4 billion dollars,"},{"time":380491,"text":"and only one percent of the drugs that start down that road"},{"time":385358,"text":"are actually going to get there."},{"time":387606,"text":"You can't imagine other businesses"},{"time":389731,"text":"that you would think of going into"},{"time":391180,"text":"that have these kind of numbers."},{"time":392935,"text":"It's a terrible business model."},{"time":394737,"text":"But it is really a worse social model because of"},{"time":398726,"text":"what's involved and the cost to all of us."},{"time":402054,"text":"So the way we develop drugs now"},{"time":405806,"text":"is by testing promising compounds on --"},{"time":409006,"text":"We didn't have disease modeling with human cells,"},{"time":410886,"text":"so we'd been testing them on cells of mice"},{"time":414350,"text":"or other creatures or cells that we engineer,"},{"time":418017,"text":"but they don't have the characteristics of the diseases"},{"time":421078,"text":"that we're actually trying to cure."},{"time":423414,"text":"You know, we're not mice, and you can't go into"},{"time":426460,"text":"a living person with an illness"},{"time":428878,"text":"and just pull out a few brain cells or cardiac cells"},{"time":431806,"text":"and then start fooling around in a lab to test"},{"time":434095,"text":"for, you know, a promising drug."},{"time":437656,"text":"But what you can do with human stem cells, now,"},{"time":441241,"text":"is actually create avatars, and you can create the cells,"},{"time":445578,"text":"whether it's the live motor neurons"},{"time":447545,"text":"or the beating cardiac cells or liver cells"},{"time":450555,"text":"or other kinds of cells, and you can test for drugs,"},{"time":454664,"text":"promising compounds, on the actual cells"},{"time":457789,"text":"that you're trying to affect, and this is now,"},{"time":461420,"text":"and it's absolutely extraordinary,"},{"time":464234,"text":"and you're going to know at the beginning,"},{"time":467390,"text":"the very early stages of doing your assay development"},{"time":471134,"text":"and your testing, you're not going to have to wait 13 years"},{"time":474523,"text":"until you've brought a drug to market, only to find out"},{"time":477842,"text":"that actually it doesn't work, or even worse, harms people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482898,"text":"But it isn't really enough just to look at"},{"time":487238,"text":"the cells from a few people or a small group of people,"},{"time":491020,"text":"because we have to step back."},{"time":492664,"text":"We've got to look at the big picture."},{"time":494515,"text":"Look around this room. We are all different,"},{"time":497651,"text":"and a disease that I might have,"},{"time":500391,"text":"if I had Alzheimer's disease or Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":503268,"text":"it probably would affect me differently than if"},{"time":507034,"text":"one of you had that disease,"},{"time":508675,"text":"and if we both had Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":513020,"text":"and we took the same medication,"},{"time":515288,"text":"but we had different genetic makeup,"},{"time":518035,"text":"we probably would have a different result,"},{"time":520320,"text":"and it could well be that a drug that worked wonderfully"},{"time":524051,"text":"for me was actually ineffective for you,"},{"time":527630,"text":"and similarly, it could be that a drug that is harmful for you"},{"time":532322,"text":"is safe for me, and, you know, this seems totally obvious,"},{"time":536624,"text":"but unfortunately it is not the way"},{"time":539352,"text":"that the pharmaceutical industry has been developing drugs"},{"time":542538,"text":"because, until now, it hasn't had the tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546524,"text":"And so we need to move away"},{"time":548816,"text":"from this one-size-fits-all model."},{"time":551770,"text":"The way we've been developing drugs is essentially"},{"time":554947,"text":"like going into a shoe store,"},{"time":556326,"text":"no one asks you what size you are, or"},{"time":558609,"text":"if you're going dancing or hiking."},{"time":560819,"text":"They just say, \"Well, you have feet, here are your shoes.\""},{"time":563627,"text":"It doesn't work with shoes, and our bodies are"},{"time":567227,"text":"many times more complicated than just our feet."},{"time":570699,"text":"So we really have to change this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573240,"text":"There was a very sad example of this in the last decade."},{"time":578424,"text":"There's a wonderful drug, and a class of drugs actually,"},{"time":581072,"text":"but the particular drug was Vioxx, and"},{"time":583752,"text":"for people who were suffering from severe arthritis pain,"},{"time":588128,"text":"the drug was an absolute lifesaver,"},{"time":591520,"text":"but unfortunately, for another subset of those people,"},{"time":596600,"text":"they suffered pretty severe heart side effects,"},{"time":601369,"text":"and for a subset of those people, the side effects were"},{"time":604097,"text":"so severe, the cardiac side effects, that they were fatal."},{"time":607994,"text":"But imagine a different scenario,"},{"time":612036,"text":"where we could have had an array, a genetically diverse array,"},{"time":616338,"text":"of cardiac cells, and we could have actually tested"},{"time":619964,"text":"that drug, Vioxx, in petri dishes, and figured out,"},{"time":625045,"text":"well, okay, people with this genetic type are going to have"},{"time":628789,"text":"cardiac side effects, people with these genetic subgroups"},{"time":633789,"text":"or genetic shoes sizes, about 25,000 of them,"},{"time":638933,"text":"are not going to have any problems."},{"time":641693,"text":"The people for whom it was a lifesaver"},{"time":644308,"text":"could have still taken their medicine."},{"time":645985,"text":"The people for whom it was a disaster, or fatal,"},{"time":650371,"text":"would never have been given it, and"},{"time":652462,"text":"you can imagine a very different outcome for the company,"},{"time":655045,"text":"who had to withdraw the drug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657813,"text":"So that is terrific,"},{"time":660629,"text":"and we thought, all right,"},{"time":662463,"text":"as we're trying to solve this problem,"},{"time":665222,"text":"clearly we have to think about genetics,"},{"time":667419,"text":"we have to think about human testing,"},{"time":670253,"text":"but there's a fundamental problem,"},{"time":671832,"text":"because right now, stem cell lines,"},{"time":674531,"text":"as extraordinary as they are,"},{"time":676241,"text":"and lines are just groups of cells,"},{"time":677985,"text":"they are made by hand, one at a time,"},{"time":682317,"text":"and it takes a couple of months."},{"time":684541,"text":"This is not scalable, and also when you do things by hand,"},{"time":688907,"text":"even in the best laboratories,"},{"time":690450,"text":"you have variations in techniques,"},{"time":693611,"text":"and you need to know, if you're making a drug,"},{"time":696792,"text":"that the Aspirin you're going to take out of the bottle"},{"time":698690,"text":"on Monday is the same as the Aspirin"},{"time":701130,"text":"that's going to come out of the bottle on Wednesday."},{"time":703211,"text":"So we looked at this, and we thought, okay,"},{"time":707002,"text":"artisanal is wonderful in, you know, your clothing"},{"time":710154,"text":"and your bread and crafts, but"},{"time":713098,"text":"artisanal really isn't going to work in stem cells,"},{"time":716081,"text":"so we have to deal with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718471,"text":"But even with that, there still was another big hurdle,"},{"time":722391,"text":"and that actually brings us back to"},{"time":725955,"text":"the mapping of the human genome, because"},{"time":728339,"text":"we're all different."},{"time":731050,"text":"We know from the sequencing of the human genome"},{"time":733882,"text":"that it's shown us all of the A's, C's, G's and T's"},{"time":736439,"text":"that make up our genetic code,"},{"time":738907,"text":"but that code, by itself, our DNA,"},{"time":743176,"text":"is like looking at the ones and zeroes of the computer code"},{"time":747775,"text":"without having a computer that can read it."},{"time":750600,"text":"It's like having an app without having a smartphone."},{"time":753888,"text":"We needed to have a way of bringing the biology"},{"time":757772,"text":"to that incredible data,"},{"time":759981,"text":"and the way to do that was to find"},{"time":763096,"text":"a stand-in, a biological stand-in,"},{"time":765783,"text":"that could contain all of the genetic information,"},{"time":769808,"text":"but have it be arrayed in such a way"},{"time":772336,"text":"as it could be read together"},{"time":775200,"text":"and actually create this incredible avatar."},{"time":778456,"text":"We need to have stem cells from all the genetic sub-types"},{"time":782160,"text":"that represent who we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785112,"text":"So this is what we've built."},{"time":787872,"text":"It's an automated robotic technology."},{"time":791192,"text":"It has the capacity to produce thousands and thousands"},{"time":793800,"text":"of stem cell lines. It's genetically arrayed."},{"time":798039,"text":"It has massively parallel processing capability,"},{"time":801788,"text":"and it's going to change the way drugs are discovered,"},{"time":805108,"text":"we hope, and I think eventually what's going to happen"},{"time":808943,"text":"is that we're going to want to re-screen drugs,"},{"time":811142,"text":"on arrays like this, that already exist,"},{"time":813633,"text":"all of the drugs that currently exist,"},{"time":815504,"text":"and in the future, you're going to be taking drugs"},{"time":818415,"text":"and treatments that have been tested for side effects"},{"time":821287,"text":"on all of the relevant cells,"},{"time":823590,"text":"on brain cells and heart cells and liver cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826743,"text":"It really has brought us to the threshold"},{"time":830072,"text":"of personalized medicine."},{"time":832286,"text":"It's here now, and in our family,"},{"time":836727,"text":"my son has type 1 diabetes,"},{"time":839665,"text":"which is still an incurable disease,"},{"time":842313,"text":"and I lost my parents to heart disease and cancer,"},{"time":845755,"text":"but I think that my story probably sounds familiar to you,"},{"time":849488,"text":"because probably a version of it is your story."},{"time":853718,"text":"At some point in our lives, all of us,"},{"time":857662,"text":"or people we care about, become patients,"},{"time":860398,"text":"and that's why I think that stem cell research"},{"time":863007,"text":"is incredibly important for all of us."},{"time":866390,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":870058,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}